<%- include('partials/head', {
  title,
  metaTitle,
  metaDescription,
  canonicalPath
}) %>

<%- include('partials/header') %>

<%
  const s = settings || {};
  const phoneRaw = String(s.phone || "").trim();
  const phoneTel = phoneRaw.replace(/\s+/g, "");
%>

<div class="wrap">
  <div class="card">
    <h1 style="color: var(--accent);">Truck Hearse FAQ</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Answers to common questions about truck hearse hire, lorry hearse hire, alternative funeral transport,
      and our specialist hearses available across the UK.
    </p>

    <div class="cta" style="margin: 18px 0 8px;">
      <a class="btn" href="/contact">Enquire</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/gallery">View gallery</a>
      <% if (phoneTel) { %>
        <a class="btn" href="tel:<%= phoneTel %>">Call <%= phoneRaw %></a>
      <% } %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:20px;">
    <h2 class="section-title" style="color: var(--accent);">What is a truck hearse?</h2>
    <div class="rich">
      <p>
        A truck hearse is an alternative funeral vehicle based on a heavy goods vehicle or large truck,
        adapted and presented for funeral use. A truck hearse offers families and funeral directors a distinctive
        and respectful alternative to a traditional hearse, especially when the person being remembered had a strong
        connection to haulage, transport, mechanics, road life, or HGVs.
      </p>
      <p>
        For many families, a truck hearse creates a final journey that feels more personal and meaningful than a
        standard vehicle. It can reflect a loved one’s career, interests, or personality while still maintaining
        dignity, professionalism, and visual impact on the day of the funeral.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:20px;">
    <h2 class="section-title" style="color: var(--accent);">Truck hearse vs traditional hearse</h2>
    <div class="rich">
      <p>
        A traditional hearse is usually a long, purpose-built funeral vehicle designed in the familiar style seen
        at most funerals. A truck hearse, by contrast, provides a more individual and memorable alternative.
        Both are respectful funeral vehicles, but a truck hearse is chosen when families want the final journey
        to reflect a life connected to the road, haulage, engineering, transport, or a love of large vehicles.
      </p>
      <p>
        The difference is not about reducing dignity or professionalism. It is about creating a more personal tribute.
        Where a traditional hearse offers convention, a truck hearse offers individuality. For some funerals,
        that difference is exactly what makes the service feel right.
      </p>
      <p>
        Families often compare a truck hearse and a traditional hearse when deciding how best to honour someone’s life.
        If the person was known for trucking, logistics, mechanics, or HGV driving, a truck hearse can be a fitting
        and powerful choice.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:20px;">
    <h2 class="section-title" style="color: var(--accent);">Lorry hearse hire for funerals across the UK</h2>
    <div class="rich">
      <p>
        PNW Carriage Masters offers lorry hearse hire for funerals across the UK, providing alternative funeral
        transport for funeral directors and families looking for something distinctive, personal, and memorable.
        Our specialist vehicles are available to support funerals throughout the UK mainland, helping create a
        final journey that stands apart from the ordinary.
      </p>
      <p>
        Lorry hearse hire is particularly suited to funerals for people who worked in haulage, transport,
        construction, engineering, recovery, agriculture, or related industries. It is also chosen by families
        who simply want a funeral vehicle that feels more personal than a traditional hearse.
      </p>
      <p>
        We work with the funeral profession to provide a respectful and professional service from enquiry through
        to the day itself. For pricing and availability, we recommend contacting us direct.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:20px;">
    <h2 class="section-title" style="color: var(--accent);">Case studies of completed services</h2>
    <div class="rich">
      <p>
        Families often want reassurance that alternative funeral transport can still be dignified, reliable,
        and professionally delivered. Our completed services demonstrate how a truck hearse or lorry hearse can
        become a meaningful part of a funeral while preserving the respect the occasion deserves.
      </p>
      <p>
        In many services, the vehicle becomes more than transport. It becomes part of the tribute itself.
        For drivers, mechanics, transport managers, and lifelong truck enthusiasts, the vehicle can reflect
        identity, pride, and a personal connection to the road.
      </p>
      <p>
        As this section develops, it can feature examples of completed funeral services, the type of vehicle used,
        the area covered, and why the chosen hearse was especially fitting. This kind of content is valuable both
        for families and for search visibility because it shows real-world relevance for truck hearse hire and
        lorry hearse hire across the UK.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:20px;">
    <h2 class="section-title" style="color: var(--accent);">Vehicle spotlight pages for each hearse</h2>
    <div class="rich">
      <p>
        Each specialist hearse has its own character, appearance, and presence. Vehicle spotlight pages help explain
        what makes each hearse unique and why it may be the right choice for a particular funeral.
      </p>
      <p>
        A good vehicle spotlight page can include the vehicle name, model, photographs, styling details,
        where it is available, and what type of tribute it suits best. These pages are also useful for SEO because
        they allow more detailed content around individual specialist hearses rather than keeping everything on one page.
      </p>
      <p>
        Over time, dedicated pages for each hearse can be added to expand the site further. For example, one page could
        focus on the Renault Magnum, while another could focus on the ERF EC12, each with its own gallery, description,
        and enquiry route.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:20px;">
    <h2 class="section-title">Frequently asked questions</h2>

    <h3 style="color: var(--accent);">Do you offer truck hearse hire across the UK?</h3>
    <p>
      Yes. We offer truck hearse and lorry hearse hire across the UK mainland for funeral directors and families
      seeking alternative funeral transport.
    </p>

    <h3 style="color: var(--accent);">Who chooses a lorry hearse for a funeral?</h3>
    <p>
      Lorry hearse hire is often chosen for someone with a connection to trucking, haulage, transport, mechanics,
      road life, or heavy vehicles. It is also chosen by families who want a unique and personal final journey.
    </p>

    <h3 style="color: var(--accent);">Is a truck hearse still respectful for a funeral?</h3>
    <p>
      Yes. A truck hearse is chosen to add personality and meaning to the funeral while maintaining a respectful,
      dignified, and professional presentation.
    </p>

    <h3 style="color: var(--accent);">How do I enquire about availability?</h3>
    <p>
      You can enquire through our contact page or by phone to discuss the date, location, and the type of specialist
      hearse required.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="card" style="margin-top:20px;">
    <h2 class="section-title">Explore more</h2>
    <div class="cta">
      <a class="btn" href="/gallery">Photo gallery</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/contact">Get a quote</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/">Back to home</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>
